This is pure and simple a taste delight! I did roast the asparagus (20 mins only, per other reviewers) and then chilled the asparagus in the fridge. I did not do the layering, but instead mixed all together. The tartness of the apple, the bite of the cheese, and the mellow roast of the asparagus along with the mild tang of the dressing .... oh my! Really, really yummy. I served this with lemon caper chicken and potato salad and my guests were talking about it two days after!

