What a wonderful blend of flavors! There were only two of us, so I halved the recipe, and it still came out delicious. The aspargus does not need to be cooked as long as the recipe calls for. I baked at 375 for 15 minutes, and they came out perfect. I was a little worried that the dressing was too sweet, but once I let it sit for a while, and I blended it into the salad, it was great. I couldn't find gruyere at the store, so I bought a creamy swiss cheese instead at Trader Joe's, and grated curls over the salad which worked out really well. I don't like golden delicious apples, so I used a Fuji instead. Next time, I might try the granny smith though. My boyfriend absolutely loved this salad. Am making for guests this weekend.

